=\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2000 albums]]\n[[Category:Ultraspank albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2011}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Progress\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Ultraspank]]\n| cover      = Progress (Ultraspank album).jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 30, 2000\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Industrial metal]], [[nu metal]], [[alternative metal]]\n| length     = 49:12\n| label      = [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| producer   = [[Peter Collins (record producer)|Peter Collins]]\n| prev_title = [[Ultraspank (album)|Ultraspank]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r484575|pure_url=yes}}|title=Progress - Ultraspank|publisher=[[Allmusic]]}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Progress''' is the second and final album by American [[industrial metal]] band [[Ultraspank]].  This is the only album to feature former [[Snot (band)|Snot]] drummer James \"Fed\" Carroll.\n\n== Background ==\n\n=== Album artwork ===\nThe album artwork used on this release is a picture of the [[Vacanti mouse]], which had a growth of cartilage molded on it's back to resemble a human ear.\n\n=== Sales ===\nDespite anemic sales, ''Progress'' nevertheless received positive reviews from critics both at the time of its release, and today.\n\n==Track listing==\n# \"Push\" - 3:52\n# \"Crumble\" - 3:46\n# \"Stuck\" - 3:34\n# \"Feed\" - 4:12\n# \"Smile\" - 3:59\n# \"Click\" - 4:24\n# \"Jackass\" - 3:40\n# \"Crack\" - 3:31\n# \"Invite Yourself In\" - 0:16\n# \"Thanks\" - 3:03\n# \"Left\" - 4:15\n# \"Where\" - 10:40\n* \"Maybe Tomorrow\" - hidden track that begins at 7:30 after \"Where\".\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Pete Murray (American musician)|Pete Murray]] - vocals, programming\n*Dan Ogden - bass guitar\n*James \"Fed\" Carroll - drums\n*Jerry Oliviera - guitar\n*Neil Godfrey - guitar\n*Peter Collins - production, 